# =============================================================================
# CODEOWNERS — who gets auto-requested as a reviewer when files change.
# =============================================================================
# Syntax:  <path pattern>   @github-username-or-team
#
# The last matching line wins. So put the most-specific rules at the bottom.
# Whoever is listed here is automatically requested to review any PR that
# touches the matching files. Combine this with "Require review from
# CODEOWNERS" in branch protection to make sure nothing merges without the
# right eyes on it.
#
# TODO: Replace `@cslmn` below with the GitHub usernames of each co-founder.
# Add more rules as you specialize (e.g., a `/ios` owner once you add native
# iOS code).
# =============================================================================

# Default — every PR asks this user (or team) for review.
*                         @cslmn

# Critical infra — only owners should touch these.
/.github/                 @cslmn
/.husky/                  @cslmn
/package.json             @cslmn
/eslint.config.mjs        @cslmn
/tsconfig.base.json       @cslmn

# Feature areas (add co-founders here as each person takes ownership).
# /apps/mobile/src/features/auth/     @cslmn @cofounder-username
# /apps/mobile/src/features/feed/     @cslmn @cofounder-username
